column5: Hitting the shallow bay with a friend for pike and maybe some bass.

I love thanksgiving weekend!  Friday after work I'm heading to the Ellmvale fall fair to take part in a fundraiser for my volunteer SAR team.  Cooking hot dogs and burgers at the tractor pull.  From there heading to the cottage on Six Mile.  Duck hunting in the morning Saturday, then sighting in the shotgun scope in the aft.  Sunday heading to the family farm in Peterborough for a day with the family.  Monday morning is up in the air.  1 of 3.  Duck hunting in Ramera, Duck Hunting/Salmon fishing on G-Bay, or Deer hunting in Innisfil..   Have a safe and enjoyable weekend everyone
Hey Splash fished from 7-10:30 and went 3/4 on lake erie steelhead
somewhere around the area perhaps by myself? local honeyhole spots...
I am swinging my way up towards Owen Sound and area.  Will be targeting pike and rainbows on the river banks.  Sleeping in the van and following the wind.  How about you all ?
I will be targetting keeping the family happy for a Thanksgiving get together....  ...brownie points you know, so I can go Muskie fishing every day there after...

I'll be fishing in the sturgeon river for walleye and muskies and maybe we'll do some Marten river area Walleye fishing also!  It's fall time ... meaning it's time to get out there when most people are hunting , hardcore anglers like us are fishing the lakes by our selves  :)  Most people don't know how exciting the fall bite is ! Don't miss it ! Dress warm and get out there!!!!
sposed to be nice and sunny here so i may get out for some eyes over the weekend. Marked a spot last weekend so gonna get serious with it on sunday.

I am going to visit my folks with my family and fish the lake they are on for any fish with teeth...  I might even bring a rod for the visit with my wife's side of the family for some fishing time in Ballsover.  That I have to play by ear...
Possibly perch on Saturday, the "eyes have it" on Sunday, perch and pike on Monday.  Fishing, fishing, and more fishing...now there is something to be THANKFUL for!!!!!!!!!!
Myself and the poster formerly known as troutologist will be chasing Superior Steel this weekend.  All of this will coalesce in a massive beer/chicken wing binge once we return to town.

I definitely wanna see Jay and the Doc's report....Splashopper has the right idea too...sleepin' in a van down by the river....dang those were the good'ol days!!!  I will content myself with a bit of smallie action in Minden, and have a 50/50 chance on some night-time shore fishing for eyes as well.

Johnny.  Look up Four Mile lake and see if you want to take a bit of a drive from Minden.  I won't be far and I still have my tinny in the water.  I'm going up Friday night and my Sat. is open for fishing as we don't have a family thing on Sat.  PM me if you want, cheers. Geoff

A bunch of family will be at Kincardine I'll be stopping in to say hi & getting the boat out for some Bass & Pike action I hope, local Lakes or maybe Baie du Dore if the winds are right, I could see some nice Pike in our future Richard
I might be near your inlaws with Dutchy on Saturday... chasing the bass and possibly those baby pike you catch there...

The family is "stealing" one last weekend by renting a cottage on Sandy Lake.  This isn't really a fishing trip but the guys will get out every chance possible. We'll probably play on Sandy Lake for awhile but try to get a full day over at Lower Buckhorn.  Any advice is sure welcome as it's a first time for all of us at this location.  Last year we rented in Brit and out of shear luck landed a couple big pike so hopefully luck will return. Snowed on us too..

Saturday  My daughter has a hockey game at 11:45am  My son has a hockey game at 5:10pm and practice at 7pm at his home rink. Should be an interesting evening. At least I get out of Thanksgiving dinner with the wife's family.   Sunday and Monday are up in the air.  I'm doing some renovations in the kitchen. I have some smaller jobs to keep me busy until the new counter tops arrive.  I also have to finish the brake job on my truck. Only did the rear.  Going to try and get out bow hunting.
I can only fish friday and its Erie trib steel I will be chasin.
If its warm and sunny going to give river smallmouth one more shot
Trolling Adolphus Reach for monster eyes on BOQ
I will be fishing for eyes with the 7mm for moose close by...it is hunting season ya know!

I have to spend the day with my family saturday and the inlaws Sunday afternoon. Of course I'll be near some east tributaries so I am packing my gear to fish steelhead, while they all sleep in I'll be fishin.
Might give Pike a try this weekend with my dad.

Got some cooked maize left over from my last carp outing so if I get a chance carp is what I may be chasing this weekend...  The latest I've caught any was Oct 05 last year before I retired my carp gear for the season...
Rainbows and maybe skein a few mud shark there chewing big hunks of pink skien right now

Well, things could not have turned out better. Was supposed to have the family + the outlaws (son-in-laws family) up to the cottage for a Thanksgiving weekend (= more cooking/entertaining & less fishing) pending the birth of a grandchild which was due Sept. 30th. As it turns out, my daughter is 'past due' and scheduled for induced labour tomorrow morning (meaning the baby should arrive sometime Friday or Saturday). So get this; the 'women-folk' don't want the men (except for son-in-law) hanging around and getting in the way. We recieved our marching orders last night. The men are to retreat to the cottage and stay away until Sunday or Monday. They'll let us know when to come home. Honest to goodness, true story. So we'll be fishing for pike & walleye. The ladies (& son-in-law) will be fishing for a baby.
Well I'll be at the cottage so I'm sure all of you can figure out what I'm fishing for!

Plans just changed.  If anyone has a spot, I'd love to get out!  I'm located in TO and a die hard fisherman for everything but carp. If not I will probably hit up some rivers and maybe some local pike or brown haunts.
